# Lessons learned (don't relearn the hard way)

When you figure out a tricky, non-obvious **technical** problem (races, cache,
network, blocking, correctness), **append a short entry below** so it isn‚Äôt lost.
Skip obvious UI polish (colors, icon choice, spacing, copy). Format each as
**symptom ‚Üí cause ‚Üí fix** in 1‚Äì3 lines. Newest first. Keep it tight; prune duplicates.

## Lessons

- **‚ÄúNo internet‚Äù banner stuck after Wi‚ÄëFi returns.** Cause: NetInfo
  `isConnected`/`isInternetReachable` stay stale offline after reconnect, and
  the listener re-applied offline after `/health` cleared; if the API host was
  also unreachable the banner never cleared. Fix: never trust raw NetInfo
  offline ‚Äî `resolveIsOffline()` requires NetInfo + health + public
  generate_204 all fail; online NetInfo still clears immediately.
- **Login ‚ÄúRate limit unavailable‚Äù / auth 429 with API healthy.** Cause: Upstash free tier
  hit max-requests; REST limiter fails closed on any Redis error, and token issue needs Redis
  too. Fix: point local `REDIS_URL` at Homebrew Redis (`redis://127.0.0.1:6379`); keep Upstash
  for prod. Expo `react` must stay on SDK pin (`19.2.3` for Expo 57) ‚Äî Dependabot patch bumps
  break Hermes boot with `property is not writable`.
- **CO‚ÇÇ diagram looked like O‚ÇÇ.** Cause: smiles-drawer skeletal mode hides chain carbons
  (`O=C=O` ‚Üí only ‚ÄúO=O‚Äù labels). Fix: after `processGraph`, set `drawExplicit` on every C
  before `drawVertices`.
- **Chemistry SMILES WebView: ‚ÄúCould not render that structure.‚Äù** Cause: smiles-drawer
  2.1.7 `Drawer.draw(..., infoOnly)` forwards `infoOnly` as `SvgDrawer`‚Äôs `weights`, so
  `false.every` throws (caught as parse/draw failure). Fix: use `SvgDrawer` on an `<svg>`
  and call `draw(tree, el, theme)` with no 4th arg.
- **Image-gen sheet came back after ‚Äúcomposer only‚Äù.** Cause: attach row was removed but
  `useChatSend` still opened `ImageGenPromptSheet` on intent. Fix: delete the sheet + call
  `submitPrompt` on send. Rule: replace UX ‚Üí delete old path (chat-ux-bans).
- **Inline fractions need a real vinculum stack, not `¬π‚îÄ‚ÇÇ` / `¬Ω` / `m/m`.** Fake
  single-line hacks don‚Äôt look like school fractions. MathText stacks num / hairline
  bar / den as a nested `View` inside `Text`, and bumps `lineHeight` when a `\frac`
  is present so the stack doesn‚Äôt clip adjacent prose.
- **Raw `(\frac{...})` inline math on screen.** Model `\(...\)` survived preprocess, then
  CommonMark escaped `\(`/`\)` to bare parens before `splitInlineMath` ‚Äî MathText never
  ran. Also `looksLikeProseParenthetical` counted `\neq`/`\frac` letter-runs as English.
  Fix (#450): convert `\(...\)` ‚Üí `$...$` in `protectMathEscapes`; strip `\\[a-zA-Z]+`
  before the prose-word count; wrap bare cmds outside existing `$` spans.
- **Chat ‚Äúfalls then snaps back‚Äù when stream ends.** Two bugs stacked: (1) intentional
  `STREAM_LAYOUT_SETTLE_MS` (280ms) hold before revealing full markdown/feedback/sources;
  (2) FlashList native autoscroll re-armed the instant streaming ended ‚Äî same moment the
  row grows ‚Äî so native snap hit the pre-growth height, then deferred JS `scrollToEnd`
  corrected again. Fix (#445): keep native autoscroll suppressed through that settle
  window too; one writer for the transition (JS), not two fighting.
- **Streaming math boxes flicker (blank ‚Üí repaint).** Pending stream tail re-parsed
  every flush; `react-native-markdown-display` re-keys the tree so KaTeX WebViews in that
  tail remount. Short closed ` ```math ` / `$$` blocks sat under the 320-char settle
  threshold for many flushes. Fix (#443): `advanceStreamBlocks` eagerly cuts at the next
  safe blank line once a fence/`$$` has closed ‚Äî don‚Äôt wait on char volume.
- **Chat cold start pulled Mermaid/Vega/MathJax.** Static imports from `RichFence` /
  `mathHtml` evaluated ~6MB of inlined vendors on every markdown message graph load.
  Fix: `React.lazy` Chart/Mermaid via `LazyHeavyRich`; MathJax in `mathHtmlMathjax`
  loaded only for multline/eqnarray when a WebView can mount.
- **Drawer menu needs many taps after Reanimated migrate.** Opaque left-edge hit strip
  (`zIndex` 210) sat on the hamburger; failed pan `onFinalize` also raced `settle(false)`
  against `open()`. Fix: `manualActivation` (claim only after horizontal move) + settle
  cancel only if the pan actually activated.
- **RNSVG ‚ÄúCodegen didn't run‚Äù flood.** Metro `resolveRequest` used Node `require.resolve('react-native-svg')` ‚Üí `lib/commonjs`, skipping package.json `"react-native": "src/"`. Fabric babel codegen never ran. Dedupe via Metro's resolver with a pinned `originModulePath` instead.
- **Model toggles snap back mid-flip.** Controlled Switch waited on Auth context; racing
  bootstrap `updateMe({timezone|location}).then(setUser)` replaced the whole user with
  stale `enabled_models`. Fix: local draft prefs; `updateUser` generation guard; bootstrap
  merges only patched fields (`useBootstrapSync`).
- **Memory screen always waits on network.** Settings already `GET /memories` for the count,
  then `/memory` refetched from empty. Fix: shared `memoryListCache` (20s TTL + inflight
  dedupe); prefetch on Settings‚ÜíMemory; hydrate on mount; invalidate on logout.
- **Header actions flicker while a chat is open.** `hasMessages={messages.length > 0}` drops
  the action group if the list briefly clears during load/refetch. Gate on
  `messages.length > 0 || routeChatId` so an active chat route keeps controls mounted.
- **iOS Simulator soft keyboard missing.** Host Connect Hardware Keyboard hides it.
  `defaults write com.apple.iphonesimulator ConnectHardwareKeyboard -bool false` (+ device
  prefs) and relaunch; ‚åòK if needed. osascript cannot toggle Simulator without Accessibility.
- **TTS 502 ‚âÝ API down.** OpenRouter 400: bare `openai/gpt-4o-mini-tts` does not exist ‚Äî
  use dated slug `openai/gpt-4o-mini-tts-2025-12-15`. `/speech/tts` 502 while the rest of
  the API stays healthy is a model-id bug, not an API outage.
- **WS ASGI Traceback on navigate.** `WebSocketDisconnect(1000)` while `chat_websocket` waits
  for auth JSON = client closed mid-reconnect; noisy, not a fatal server failure.
- **Image goes blurry/gray after the assistant replies.** Focus refetch after `streaming‚Üífalse` replaces `local-*` ids with server UUIDs; id-only `mergeLocalAttachmentUris` dropped `local_image_uri` and restarted blur reveal. Also match orphaned local URIs onto incoming user attachment messages; user thumbs use `animatedReveal={false}`.
- **Attachment send showed `[BEGIN UNTRUSTED‚Ä¶]` + blurry spinner.** `wrap_untrusted` was persisted into the user message; focus refetch then dropped `local_image_uri` so ChatMessageImage remounted on a remote auth URL. Persist plain `[Image:]`/`[File:]` only; merge local URIs on refetch; skip blur reveal for `file://`.
- **CodeQL poly-ReDoS not cleared by `collapse_ws` / length caps.** CodeQL ignores those as sanitizers; rewrite sinks to linear scans (`find` / digit parse). See `.cursor/skills/security-alert-pitfalls/SKILL.md`.
- **Dependabot on transitive npm (markdown-it@10, uuid@7).** Direct pins don't help ‚Äî use `pnpm.overrides` + regenerate lock with `npx pnpm@9.15.9 install`. See security-alert-pitfalls skill.
- **Raw LaTeX + smashed prose in math bubbles.** `normalizeImplicitMath` re-wrapped `(excluded values: $x ‚Ä¶$)` / `(e.g., ‚Ä¶ like $x^4$)` as `$‚Ä¶$$`, inventing a trailing `$$` that stole the next display-math opener ‚Äî equations showed raw and Wait‚Äîprose became a MathBlock (italic, no spaces). Fix: skip parens that already contain `$` or look like English prose (2+ letter-words).
- **SecureStore Keychain ‚Äúrequired entitlement isn‚Äôt present‚Äù on simulator.** Linker-signed/adhoc builds (`TeamIdentifier=not set`, no identities) get `errSecMissingEntitlement` (-34018) on `setItemAsync`. Don‚Äôt put non-secrets (list order) in SecureStore ‚Äî use filesystem; catch SecureStore writes. Proper Keychain needs a local Apple signing identity + `expo run:ios` rebuild.
- **Quiz wrong-answer UX: hint only, no re-render.** User rejected re-asking the same MCQ
  after a miss. Prompts must not emit a new ```vocab_quiz on wrong; chips stay on the prior
  quiz message (`findActiveQuizMessageId`). Grade against `get_last_quiz_assistant`, not the
  hint-only last assistant.
- **Quiz answers ‚Äúdon‚Äôt register‚Äù (Today stays 0/x).** Causes: (1) nested `session.commit()` in
  `messages.create` / `apply_quiz_result` mid‚Äìturn_prep; (2) letter answer + missing `vocab_quiz`
  fence ‚Üí grade `None` and `skip_memory_jobs` blocked background sync; (3) My Learning 20s stale
  cache. Fix: `commit=False` until one outer commit; don‚Äôt skip jobs when letter grade fails;
  force-refresh projects list/detail on focus; invalidate home after grade.
- **Unpushed local diffs cause real pain.** User runs other machines/simulators off `main` /
  remote ‚Äî finish every change with commit + push (see `execution.mdc`); don't say done with
  local-only work.
- **User rejected ‚ÄúRecalled N memories‚Äù chip + assistant Show more/less.** Do not reintroduce ‚Äî
  see `.cursor/rules/chat-ux-bans.mdc`. Code-block fold only; assistant body stays unfolded.
- **User rejected model-fallback / context-summarized chips** (`chat.model_fallback` raw key
  flashed in chat). Do not reintroduce ‚Äî see chat-ux-bans ¬ß4.
- **`ERR_PNPM_LOCKFILE_CONFIG_MISMATCH` on patchedDependencies.** Regenerating `pnpm-lock.yaml`
  with pnpm 11 drops patch metadata while `package.json` still declares patches; CI uses pnpm 9 and
  fails frozen install. Regenerate with `npx pnpm@9.15.9 install` (or pin `"packageManager"`).
- **Simulator can't reach LAN API URL.** Physical device needs `EXPO_PUBLIC_API_URL=http://<lan-ip>:8000`
  (`./scripts/set-lan-ip.sh`); iOS Simulator needs `http://127.0.0.1:8000` (`./scripts/set-sim-ip.sh`
  or `./scripts/dev.sh mobile-sim`). Wrong URL ‚Üí login/chat fails with network errors, not a code bug.
- **"Coverage is failing" but really lint/types are.** CI order is `ruff check ‚Üí ruff format
  --check ‚Üí mypy ‚Üí pytest --cov-fail-under=80`; an earlier step failing means pytest never runs.
  Run the whole chain locally before committing, not just pytest.
- **Unpinned dev tooling silently breaks CI.** `mypy`/`ruff` were `>=`, so CI pulled a newer,
  stricter mypy and failed. Keep them capped in `pyproject.toml` and pin Python (`<3.14`).
- **SQLAlchemy `.rowcount` fails mypy.** `await session.execute(delete(...))` is typed `Result`
  (no `.rowcount`) ‚Üí `cast(CursorResult[Any], await session.execute(...))`. Also never
  `from sqlalchemy import update` in a repo that defines its own `update()` (F811 shadow ‚Üí wrong
  symbol at type-check).
- **mypy won't narrow a doubled `.get()`.** `usage.get("x") if usage.get("x") is not None else ‚Ä¶`
  stays `int | None`. Assign to a local first, then branch on the local.
- **HTML/JS WebView preview "not working" = wrong build, not a bug.** `react-native-webview` is a
  native module; it never works in Expo Go. Rebuild the dev client (`pnpm expo run:ios`). It
  falls back to static HTML (scripts stripped) otherwise.
- **System dark mode on a static `C` palette.** Keep `C` (light) for unmigrated screens; add
  `useTheme()` and convert module-level `StyleSheet.create` into `makeX(t: Theme)` factories
  called via `useMemo`. Low-churn and incremental.
- **Mobile deps won't install in this env.** npm points at an auth-gated internal registry, so
  `tsc`/Expo can't run here ‚Äî verify mobile changes with `pnpm typecheck`/`pnpm lint` locally.
- **expo-av / voice crash (`ExponentAV` not found).** `expo-av` is incompatible with SDK 56 ‚Äî use
  `expo-audio` instead; lazy-load via `lib/voiceAudio.ts` for Expo Go; rebuild dev client with
  `pnpm expo run:ios` (not Expo Go).
